The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, April 2: The US economy will not grow much in the first half of this year and could even contract slightly, Federal Reserve chairman Ben Bernanke warned today, hinting at the possibility of the start of a recession. In prepared remarks to the joint economic committee, he, however, did not use the word recession and also held out the possibility of the economy strengthening in the second half of the year.                            
	 Mumbai, April 2: Tata Consultancy Services equity capital has risen to Rs 220 crore from Rs 120 crore after the allotment of 100 crore redeemable preference shares of Re 1 each at par to Tata Sons. The redeemable preference shares are not being listed on any bourses.                            
	 Mumbai, April 2: The SBI will issue five-year yen-denominated bonds worth Rs 468 crore on April 8. The bonds will carry a coupon rate of 3.36 per cent.                            
	 Mumbai, April 2: Spice Communications is in talks with some foreign players, including AT amp;T and Emirates Telecommunications, for a possible collaboration in the Indian telecom market.                            
	 Mumbai, April 2: NTPC Ltd has floated a joint venture company with Uttar Pradesh Rajya Vidyut Utpadan Nigam to set up a 1,320MW power plant in the state.
                                                                                                                           
